article.headline: Lipscomb 80, Fisk 68
article.story: NASHVILLE, Tenn. (AP) -- Brian Fisk led Lipscomb with 22 points in a 80-68 win over Fisk Saturday night. The Bisons (3-2) were also helped by Trey Williams with 17 points and six rebounds and Eddie Ard with 15 points and seven rebounds. Fisk (0-3) took the lead less than two minutes into the game and still was leading 44-36 at the end of the first half. Lipscomb did not come back until the 9:59 mark of the second half and Fisk tied the game twice in the final 8 1/2 minutes. In the final 3:39, with a 66-62 lead, the Bisons went on a 14-6 run. Michael Glaze led the Bulldogs with 18 points and seven rebounds. Marquies Patton followed with 12 points and seven rebounds and Jonathan Pillow scored 11 points and another 11 rebounds.
